5000|$|Tragopogon pratensis (common names <b>Jack-go-to-bed-at-noon,</b> meadow salsify, showy goat's-beard or meadow goat's-beard) is a {{biennial}} {{plant in}} the Asteraceae family, distributed across Europe and North America, commonly growing in fields (hence its name) and on roadsides. It is found in North America from southern Ontario to Massachusetts; most of England; on the eastern and southern edges of Scotland; and central Ireland but not the coastal edges.|$|E

